The paper discusses a technology that enables secure and private execution of smart contracts over private data. This involves the integration of a distributed ledger and Intel Secure Guard Extensions (SGX). The paper focuses on security and privacy aspects of the technology, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the categories of cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE).
